{"title":"Sharing the love with Netlify Deployment Badges","preview":"e’ve heard how much you love Netlify deployments and seeing them happen as if by magic. And it’s only natural: getting changes in the hands of your users is one of the best feelings in the world. If y...","slug":"sharing-the-love-with-netlify-deployment-badges-nuf7no","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">e’ve heard how much you love Netlify deployments and seeing them happen as if by magic. And it’s only natural: getting changes in the hands of your users is one of the best feelings in the world. If you’re anything like us, you can’t wait to announce that a new feature is finally live!</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We have previously built different ways to get deploy&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/webhooks/#outgoing-webhooks-and-notifications\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">notifications</a>, some of them right from your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2018/05/22/netlify-now-shows-your-deploy-status-on-its-favicon/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">browser tabs</a>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Today, we are happy to announce that you can see the status of your most recent deployment, right from your repository or website, using Netlify Deployment Badges!</p><div><h2 id=\"show-me-your-badges\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Show me your badges</h2><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Representing achievements or interests as badges is not a new concept online or offline. From gaming, to social systems, and even traveling, badges have been a fun way of engaging and motivating users, building reputation, or simply showcasing interests.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Badges bring an underlying feeling of commitment and transparency that have made them highly sought-after and rapidly adopted by open-source projects. They’re an easy way of instilling confidence the project is actively maintained and cared for by the community.</p><h2 id=\"how-we-built-the-feature\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">How we built the feature</h2><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><strong>It all started…with you!</strong></p></div>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557968888910},"_id":"DORBio7pB6dh33TF"}
{"title":"Deploy CodeSandbox to Netlify","preview":"Here at Netlify we love developer tools. We focus a lot of attention on making the experience of building for the web as simple and powerful as we can, and the evolution of development tooling contrib...","slug":"deploy-codesandbox-to-netlify-wm92ku","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Here at Netlify we love developer tools. We focus a lot of attention on making the experience of building for the web as simple and powerful as we can, and the evolution of development tooling contributes to this a great deal.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">So, in April 2017, when&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/bazzjuh\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Bas Buursma</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/CompuIves\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Ives van Hoorne</a>&nbsp;launched CodeSandbox, an IDE that you use right from the web browser, we watched with great interest.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Today, we are happy to announce that you’re now able to create and deploy sites to Netlify, directly from CodeSandbox!</p><h2 id=\"what-is-codesandbox\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">What is CodeSandbox?</h2><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">An impressive browser-based IDE built with React and a lot of ingenuity,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">CodeSandbox</a>&nbsp;has steadily matured and improved since its launch. And has become a fantastic tool for building and experimenting. All from your web browser without the need to create a local development environment. It’s remarkable.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">After introducing&nbsp;<a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/codesandbox-containers-5864a8f26715\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">CodeSandbox containers</a>, it gained the ability to execute the parts of your code that you might usually use as a build step on your local machine. This made it even more enticing to use with JAMstack projects, which you could then deploy to Netlify.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">There are already a number of ways to deploy a site to Netlify:</p><ol style=\"margin: 1.618em 0px 1.618em 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><li>Using our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://app.netlify.com/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">app.netlify.com</a>&nbsp;UI (<a href=\"https://serverless.com/blog/how-built-static-serverless-website-netlify/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">tutorial</a>)</li><li>Running&nbsp;<code style=\"background: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.09); border: 2px solid transparent; color: rgb(14, 30, 37); font-family: &quot;Roboto Mono&quot;, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, &quot;Liberation Mono&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 0.8em; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">netlify deploy</code>&nbsp;via the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://cli.netlify.com/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">command line</a></li><li>Clicking the mighty&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/deploy-button/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">deploy to Netlify button</a></li><li>Calling the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://open-api.netlify.com/#/default/createSite\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Netlify API</a></li><li>Defining your site in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/netlify/index.html\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">terraform</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2018/11/29/deploying-netlify-sites-with-aws-cloudformation/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Via AWS CloudFormation</a></li><li><strong>…and now, CodeSandbox deployments!</strong></li></ol><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Today’s announcement adds yet another method of creating and deploying Netlify to sites. This new integration was built in collaboration with the team at CodeSandbox and we’re delighted at how it can shorten the path between writing code, and getting your sites online.</p>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557967546989},"_id":"GpGFty0z7pyH7GBR"}
{"title":"Featured site: Proxx. A site by Google Chrome Labs","preview":"For Google I/O 2019, the Google Chrome Labs team designed and built a game using web technologies. The game, Proxx is an exploration (by the same team at Google who built undefinedProxx makes use of t...","slug":"featured-site-proxx-a-site-by-google-chrome-labs-4kms3m","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For Google I/O 2019, the Google Chrome Labs team designed and built a game using web technologies. The game,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://proxx.app/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Proxx</a>&nbsp;is heavily inspired by Minesweeper, the old classic many of us will remember from Windows back in the&nbsp;<em>(choose a decade and show your age)</em>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Proxx is an exploration (by the same team at Google who built&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2019/01/09/featured-site-squoosh.app/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Squoosh.app</a>, also hosted by Netlify) into building interactive, dynamic, and performant applications with web technologies. It is a super example of optimizing for performance without sacrificing capabilities, and has wonderfully broad compatibility.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/bpkXfnWdVzyGd_EjarQ6-WOqz7M6XtmUjMncE8jWlHfKuimp0EQJ-3Cuq2PYN4sVI-8XPnWegk3Y7vH4aHSvv4Zy=s2048\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/bpkXfnWdVzyGd_EjarQ6-WOqz7M6XtmUjMncE8jWlHfKuimp0EQJ-3Cuq2PYN4sVI-8XPnWegk3Y7vH4aHSvv4Zy\"></a></p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Proxx makes use of technologies like&nbsp;<a href=\"https://preactjs.com/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Preact</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rollupjs.org/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Rollup</a>&nbsp;for components and bundling,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">WebWorkers</a>&nbsp;for thread management, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">WebGL</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Canvas</a>&nbsp;for rendering.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Google have made&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChromeLabs/proxx\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">the source code</a>&nbsp;open source, and available as an excellent learning resource.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The app is being featured and discussed as part of a session called&nbsp;<a href=\"https://events.google.com/io/schedule/events/edd25f87-df45-4b17-84c8-2037ab1b6bae\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Build Fast and Smooth Web Apps from Feature Phone to Desktop</a>&nbsp;at Google I/O.<br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></p>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557967483649},"_id":"HGAWHjCitHUVPhgI"}
{"title":"Deep dive: How do React hooks really work?","preview":"undefinedIn this article, we reintroduce closures by building a tiny clone of React Hooks. This will serve two purposes – to demonstrate the effective use of closures, and to show how you can build a ...","slug":"deep-dive-how-do-react-hooks-really-work-d42git","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/hooks\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Hooks</a>&nbsp;are a fundamentally simpler way to encapsulate stateful behavior and side effects in user interfaces. They were&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dpw9EHDh2bM\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">first introduced in React</a>&nbsp;and have been broadly embraced by other frameworks like&nbsp;<a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/what-hooks-mean-for-vue/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Vue</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Rich_Harris/status/1093260097558581250\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Svelte</a>, and even adapted for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/getify/TNG-Hooks\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">general functional JS</a>. However, their functional design requires a good understanding of closures in JavaScript.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In this article, we reintroduce closures by building a tiny clone of React Hooks. This will serve two purposes – to demonstrate the effective use of closures, and to show how you can build a Hooks clone in just 29 lines of readable JS. Finally, we arrive at how Custom Hooks naturally arise.</p><blockquote style=\"margin-top: 2em; margin-bottom: 2em; padding: 0px 0px 0px 1.618em; border-left-width: 4px; border-left-color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.09); color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.54); font-size: 1.1em; font-style: italic; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none;\">⚠️ Note: You don’t need to do any of this in order to understand Hooks. It might just help your JS fundamentals if you go through this exercise. Don’t worry, it’s not that hard!</p></blockquote><h2 id=\"what-are-closures\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">What are Closures?</h2><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">One of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-intro.html#classes-confuse-both-people-and-machines\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">many selling points</a>&nbsp;of using hooks is to avoid the complexity of classes and higher order components altogether. However, with hooks, some feel we may have swapped one problem for another. Instead of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://overreacted.io/how-are-function-components-different-from-classes/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">worrying about bound context</a>, we now have to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://overreacted.io/making-setinterval-declarative-with-react-hooks/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">worry about closures</a>. As&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/markdalgleish/status/1095025468367990784\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Mark Dalgleish memorably summarized</a>:</p><div><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Closures are a fundamental concept in JS. In spite of this, they are notorious for being confusing to many especially newer developers. Kyle Simpson of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/getify/You-Dont-Know-JS/blob/master/scope%20%26%20closures/ch5.md\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">You Don’t Know JS</a>&nbsp;fame defines closures as such:</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><em>Closure is when a function is able to remember and access its lexical scope even when that function is executing outside its lexical scope.</em></p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">They’re obviously closely tied to the concept of lexical scoping, which&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Closures\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">MDN defines</a>as “how a parser resolves variable names when functions are nested”.</p></div>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557967618530},"_id":"U99lOZAEdmOcn73a"}
{"title":"A more flexible build architecture with updated Linux","preview":"undefinedUnder the hood, this workflow has relied on a single Our original build image was made to use We knew we wanted to upgrade to The answer came in modifying our infrastructure to accommodate mu...","slug":"a-more-flexible-build-architecture-with-updated-linux-6hbvz7","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p><span style=\"color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">One of our primary goals at Netlify is to make deployments something you don’t have to worry about. With that in mind, we designed our process for creating a site from a connected Git repository so that it “just works” with very little configuration. We get daily feedback about how much people love this!</span></p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Under the hood, this workflow has relied on a single&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/netlify/build-image\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">build image</a>&nbsp;with a variety of common languages and build tools pre-installed. We’ve made non-breaking changes to it over the years, adding support for new features without changing behavior on legacy sites. It has served us well, but the time has come where we need to make a change.</p><h2 id=\"moving-from-trusty-to-xenial\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Moving from “Trusty” to “Xenial”</h2><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Our original build image was made to use&nbsp;<a href=\"http://releases.ubuntu.com/14.04/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Ubuntu Linux 14.04 LTS</a>&nbsp;(codenamed “Trusty Tahr”). This is a stable release with long term support, but it will be reaching its&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Releases\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">end of life</a>&nbsp;in April 2019. Also, some features included in newer versions of the popular site generator&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gohugo.io/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Hugo</a>&nbsp;require a newer version of Linux.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We knew we wanted to upgrade to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/XenialXerus\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Ubuntu Linux 16.04 LTS</a>&nbsp;(codenamed “Xenial Xerus”), but unlike adding a language version or a new build tool, changing the operating system version on our build image is a potentially breaking change. We needed a way to test changes, and to roll them out selectively.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The answer came in modifying our infrastructure to accommodate multiple build images, with the ability to assign a particular build image to a site. This required collaboration from members of our platform and API teams, working together over a period of months, but it means that we can now test new changes an iterate more quickly than before.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">It also means we can roll out changes for all new sites, without affecting builds on existing sites. And that’s exactly what we’re doing today.</p>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557967584490},"_id":"lBcynRpokcsBKuwG"}
{"title":"Netlify and bandwidth","preview":"The big news today is the Coupled with the release of better asset management, we thought it was a good opportunity to bring clarity to our bandwidth packaging and overages.All Netlify plans include g...","slug":"netlify-and-bandwidth-paghe4","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The big news today is the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/blog/2019/02/26/manage-your-code-and-assets-together-with-netlify-large-media/\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">launch of Netlify Large Media</a>, powerful new functionality that allows you to manage large assets in your Git repositories, just like code.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Coupled with the release of better asset management, we thought it was a good opportunity to bring clarity to our bandwidth packaging and overages.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">All Netlify plans include generous amounts of bandwidth, but now you can purchase even more bandwidth to fuel the growth of your websites.</p><h3 id=\"included-bandwidth\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 1.3em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Included bandwidth</h3><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For our non-enterprise customers, the plan you are currently on determines the amount of bandwidth provided:</p><ul style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; margin-left: 1em; list-style-type: disc; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px;\"><li>The&nbsp;<strong>Free</strong>&nbsp;plan now includes up to 100GB of bandwidth per month</li><li>The&nbsp;<strong>Team Pro</strong>&nbsp;plan now includes up to 400GB of bandwidth per month</li><li>The&nbsp;<strong>Team Business</strong>&nbsp;plan now includes up to 600GB of bandwidth per month</li></ul><h3 id=\"bandwidth-metering-you-have-time-before-charges-apply\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 1.3em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Bandwidth metering—you have time before charges apply</h3><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">For Netlify customers, we are providing 30 days to monitor your usage before any bandwidth charges will be applied.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">You can always see your bandwidth usage in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://app.netlify.com/account/settings/billing\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">Netlify Dashboard</a>.</p><h3 id=\"purchasing-extra-bandwidth\" style=\"color: rgb(14, 30, 37); margin: 2.618em auto 0px; font-size: 1.3em; line-height: 1.333; font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Purchasing extra bandwidth</h3><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Extra bandwidth can be purchased in blocks of 100GB/mo for $20 each. Starting in April, these charges will automatically be applied as you consume bandwidth beyond your plan limits.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">You can also upgrade your account for more bandwidth along with more functionality. See our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/pricing\" style=\"color: inherit; outline-color: rgb(0, 194, 178); background-image: linear-gradient(currentcolor, currentcolor); background-origin: padding-box; background-position: center bottom 8%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 1px; position: relative; text-shadow: rgb(255, 255, 255) 3px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) 1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -1px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -2px 0px, rgb(255, 255, 255) -3px 0px; z-index: 2;\">pricing page</a>&nbsp;for details.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 1.618em; margin-bottom: 1.618em; padding: 0px; max-width: none; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Sensible, fair pricing for bandwidth will allow us to continue to develop and scale Netlify’s powerful workflow and platform for modern websites. We continue to be amazed and what you are building and can’t wait to show you what else we have in store.</p>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557968845950},"_id":"nPgE5Z3S2mR9CRqI"}
{"title":"Netlify Dev — our entire platform, right on your laptop","preview":"undefinedWhen it comes to web development, the ability to replicate your production environment is key. It brings confidence that the code you write on your local machine will behave as intended when ...","slug":"netlify-dev-our-entire-platform-right-on-your-laptop-jdtzrp","link":"","type":"","numReplies":0,"isPublic":"no","image":"","text":"<p><a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/z94JDHqjKU1osWRLdaxZMjs9rFGH22T4MNtThu9AI3GgVuJC1CVa3SxePaMeVQ0Li1yNi7pYT4xufXmO_v1_t0hi=s2048\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/z94JDHqjKU1osWRLdaxZMjs9rFGH22T4MNtThu9AI3GgVuJC1CVa3SxePaMeVQ0Li1yNi7pYT4xufXmO_v1_t0hi\"></a></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">When it comes to web development, the ability to replicate your production environment is key. It brings confidence that the code you write on your local machine will behave as intended when it is published to the world. This has been one of the many desirable aspects of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://netlify-pzipiq.turbo360-vertex.com/single#\" style=\"color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); text-decoration-line: underline; transition-duration: 0.3s; transition-property: all;\">JAMstack</a>&nbsp;sites since the beginning. Sites comprised of pre-generated assets can be deployed simply and with confidence. They are portable by default.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">But things have become a little more complicated.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">As the JAMstack ecosystem has matured, developers can now use all manner of tools and services to further enrich their sites. At Netlify, we have embraced the challenge of providing tools for developers to simplify the work of building, deploying, and serving sites on the web.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.2; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-size: 2rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Tools</span></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We provided build automation, to replicate local build pipelines.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We added a Redirects Engine to run powerful and performant redirects, proxying, and localisation services on the CDN.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We introduced Netlify Functions to bring the same immutable, atomic deployment pipelines to serverless functions, as developers have been enjoying in the rest of their codebase with Netlify for years.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">We included environment variables in Netlify, to add secrets and keys when sites are built in our CI/CD pipeline.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: rgba(14, 30, 37, 0.8); font-family: Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">And quite a bit more.</p><p><br></p>","tags":[],"dateString":"May 16, 2019","schema":"post","timestamp":{"$$date":1557967419748},"_id":"oscfDcVXaxTxHNQc"}
